originalText.text: This place change my life. I started with a free class, then I sign for a short term promotion and now I’m decided to get an  unlimited membership because I saw so many changes in my mood, my energy levels throughout the day and body armory. Ive been going in a daily basis with a day of rest and I love the results.  The energy there it’s so high it doesn’t feel that you are working out and it’s almost therapeutic for you peace of mind also. Highly recommend Nick and Meg performance classes. Their playlist and knowledge make my rides so enjoyable and worthy.

originalText.text: I have attended more than 5 classes over the last couple of weeks. I have thoroughly enjoyed my time there. I have really liked to take Lauren's class. She has such a great spirit and super energetic. Her time slot seems to also have fun themes for music so whenever I am able to make it I try to reserve my spot. The studio is located on the third floor. You can take the elevator or the stairs. There are two bathroom stalls and one changing room. There are more available on the second floor in the pure barre section and it says there are showers too. I haven't gone downstairs to use them but it's nice to know they're available. When you arrive you check in, and it's right beside where you can pick up the cycling shoes to your size. There are lockers available for leaving your stuff if needed. When you get to your assigned bike there is a fresh towel and the people who work there are readily available if you need support adjusting your bike. Overall I really have enjoyed my time there. I look forward to my next ride.

originalText.text: One word Transformative! Okay so in detail I just did one class  and overall it is an intensive workout. I can see it being a quick remedy for toned thighs for me personally as I am 5-5 with a bit more weight to my bottom and legs so the bike was a bit uncomfortable for my bottom to say the least it is adjustable for my height. The music is very motivational. The instructor was cool, she seemed to be in-tuned with all the cyclist and making it encouraging for my pace. I popped in for my first ride so I’m not sure what level I did as Dani basically did everything for me including greeting me pleasantly, checking me in, providing the shoes/towel and selecting the bike which I was directed to tune throughout cycling. I can say everyone was on track and on high energy. I was able to use my neighbor in front and next to me as a guide because it was a bit hard for me to hear the instruction and keep up. The results are shown on the bike and on the stat board above the instructor. The class was pretty much full house. I have no complaints and a membership is worthy if your into cycling as an exercise and this is coming from a beginner whom hasn’t rode a bike in over 20 years!

originalText.text: Cyclebar UES is such a great studio! The instructors have the best energy and meet you where you’re at skills-wise. Super welcoming environment from the moment you walk into the studio to the moment you leave! There are two bathrooms and a changing room in the space, and more showers and bathrooms downstairs at PureBarre that are available. 100% recommend coming in and taking Maireád, Lauren, or Nick!

originalText.text: Wow!!!! Wow!!! Wow!!!! I attended Lindsy’s 5:30 cycle class on Friday and it was spectacular! The class was sooooo much fun! Truly a blast! Lindsy made my entire trip to NYC worth it and she was the highlight of my stay here! I felt so hyped and alive once I finished. A true goddess! The entire place  was welcoming and positive and I felt like I was at a party!! The staff was kind and so helpful!!!! Def a queer friendly vibe too! 100% come check out this place!
